Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.29,0:01:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,excited pretty soon we're going to have a hundred slides wow unconsciousness level unconditional
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.70,0:01:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,love unconditional love is really at 540 and the miraculous is common at 540 540 is the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.98,0:01:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration level of 12 step groups etc of course the miracles and the miraculous occurs there all
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.65,0:01:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the time of course and so that's what people seek through spiritual healing they speak they
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.81,0:02:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what they're seeking is the reach of field in which the energy of the field is such that it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.29,0:02:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has a more powerful effect as context so we're saying that they're spontaneous they're autonomous
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.77,0:02:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they're part of the emergence of creation and the power of faith and belief potentiates their
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.12,0:02:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood the likelihood is they with faith and belief and of course constantine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.58,0:02:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrated that principle that he prayed earnestly to a god and not even the god that we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are familiar with but whatever god there might be and transformed all of western the western world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and i forgot to mention of course as a consequence of constantine emerged the council of nicaea
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.68,0:02:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course constantinople as dr kalmbach was briefing me on the history he's a history buff he
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,knows everything that ever happened in it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.81,0:03:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever my mind is bottled i'm recovering from it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.68,0:03:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,council of nicaea and of course constantinople which when editurk took over in turkey he changed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.77,0:03:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the name to uh istanbul istanbul
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.99,0:03:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,i like constantinople better but it's in blue
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so we think that when what we hope will occur
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.58,0:03:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't occur that somehow we've lost god is not answering our prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.93,0:03:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,miracles is not a possibility everybody's busy praying for healings of something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:04:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and giving god advice in all kinds of matters there's a considerable benefit in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,not hate not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,non-healing, and as I mentioned, the last pope signified that, that it is, if accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.97,0:04:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with grace, you accept that for reasons I know not, that you take on some of the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.07,0:04:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own life, and maybe even have volunteered to do so for others, for the undoing of perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,negative karmic events in the past, so if a thing doesn't heal, it doesn't mean you've
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.01,0:04:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,lost, it means that it now has taken on a different significance or meaning, I've had
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole textbook of physical illnesses in this lifetime, and any one of which should
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.64,0:05:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have killed me, and half a dozen at one time, and came close to death very, not infrequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and somehow miraculously they healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.06,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just, you know, we give testimony to the miraculous in our own life, and of course
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.58,0:05:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I'm doing now, in my own life, there were many grave illnesses, and I just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.00,0:05:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,refused regular medical treatment, and for instance, I was dying of heart failure, and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this was in Sedona, not that many years ago, 25 or so, 20 years ago, and I went to see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.45,0:05:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,an internist, and he said, well, you know, I'm going to go to Sedona, and I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.50,0:05:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,see if you've got COPD and right-hearted heart failure, there isn't anything we can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.92,0:05:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,do about it, so I went home to die, and I had a pinning edema, it's called anisarcha,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.95,0:06:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so severe that your whole body swells up right about to here, so when it gets to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.36,0:06:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the heart, you croak, so I figured, well, I put the house in order, I'm very neat, you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.64,0:06:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,know, compulsive type, make sure everything's neat and sweet and orderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And ready to go, and at the same time, I had a voracious appetite, I was eating, I figured,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.18,0:06:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,6,000 calories a day, and losing weight, I weighed about 110, and I was still director,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,chief of staff at this recovery house in Prescott Valley, so I didn't want them to know about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.49,0:06:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,my condition, so I smuggled in little oxygen tanks in my black bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.20,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then periodically, I would breathe oxygen, and because to go to the girl's ranch, you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have to go over Mingus Mountain, which is 7,200 feet, and Sedona's at 45, and the girl's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.37,0:07:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ranch is at about 6, so I smuggled oxygen in, and they wouldn't know that I was having
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this problem, and I just kept going as long as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.81,0:07:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a cop stopped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, Doc, you're not driving right today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, you better go see your doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I went to an emergency room in Cottonwood, and their wonderful doctor, an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.56,0:07:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,internist who's been my internist ever since, looked at me, and he said, that's the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,case of greatest disease I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.35,0:07:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the internist I'd seen before in Sedona, it wasn't even a differential diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.29,0:07:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He hadn't even thought of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, the thyroid was enlarged, and the protein-bound iodine, everything was way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.17,0:07:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.67,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So they said, well, we'll have to take the thyroid out surgically.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.49,0:08:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, I don't think I want to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.37,0:08:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I have my own ways of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.44,0:08:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So then they decided radiation was the way to go, and I said, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.61,0:08:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Radiation sickness, no, I don't think I'll take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.29,0:08:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, I slowly recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I take, I'll show you how we practice medicine at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We save thousands of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.20,0:08:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.05,0:08:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, my PBI is currently normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.84,0:08:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That saved $150.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to put all your colleagues out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My chest x-ray is currently normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, and the right upper apex, I mean, these are all these illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.49,0:08:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is the only opportunity I'll ever get this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to cap the bodies to tell them all my medical problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.87,0:09:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, by chest x-ray, they discovered a mass in the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.76,0:09:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the apex of the right lung.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, well, it's either neoplastic or it's something or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.64,0:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so anyway, they did a thoracentesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.14,0:09:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They stick a needle through your chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.12,0:09:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had no anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.67,0:09:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't exactly fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.72,0:09:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And the lung collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.29,0:09:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I turned blue and couldn't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.77,0:09:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And they wanted to take that out surgically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.00,0:09:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, no, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my own ways of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.24,0:09:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All these illnesses recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the chest x-ray eventually became clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:09:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a formidable procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, the lung collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.26,0:10:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you have a Graves' disease, all your joints are very painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And they want me to put my arms up underneath this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that they run you through, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.90,0:10:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And God, I couldn't stand the pain in my shoulders, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally, the guy got sort of mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.49,0:10:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, you got to put them up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.83,0:10:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.83,0:10:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you're dying of heart disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.27,0:10:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And heart failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.37,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the name of that disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.78,0:10:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I just said the Graves' disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got a neoplasm in your right upper lung.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.29,0:10:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And your lung has collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're also in heart failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than that, you're in pretty good shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.03,0:10:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, as you can see, all those things disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the good home cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.90,0:11:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was still single at the time, but they're real.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.34,0:11:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see what happens when you're single.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.34,0:11:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You get all these diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they all recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.00,0:11:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the biopsy from the apex of the right upper lobe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.88,0:11:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,said it's not neoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.32,0:11:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an incurable form of aviary tuberculosis, which can't be cured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you take about eight or 10
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.57,0:11:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,antibiotics, there's a 50% chance that you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.87,0:11:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will recover in a couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the price was $10,000 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.84,0:11:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was $10,000 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.30,0:11:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See if I'm remembering correctly, at the time, I had no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.02,0:11:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So $10,000 a month seemed like a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was $10,000 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.37,0:11:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, oh my god, it was $10,000 a month, about six or eight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.49,0:12:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,exotic antibiotics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would make you sick and nauseous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were sick and nauseous spending $10,000 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.99,0:12:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With a 50-50 chance, they're just going to cure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.42,0:12:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't seem like too good a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, whatever cured all the other ailments of the lung.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also have atelectasis, which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.73,0:12:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,means a part of your lung has collapsed, which I probably
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.27,0:12:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,still have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, you just don't pay attention to these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.12,0:12:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just keep doing the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.62,0:12:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just keep forgiving, and you just follow
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.77,0:12:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your spiritual pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And either they heal or they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.53,0:12:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, well, if they heal, you live.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.27,0:12:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they don't, then you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.44,0:12:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So there were many illnesses like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a pilonidal cyst in the back of the base of the spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.84,0:12:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's surgical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.24,0:12:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to take it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.65,0:13:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I picture that as disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.24,0:13:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have surgery for that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I had so many illnesses, I forget them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, I'd gout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I had all these at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.33,0:13:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'd gout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.15,0:13:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to keep emergency gout medicine in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.67,0:13:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you could be walking down the sidewalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.08,0:13:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and gout is weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.05,0:13:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It hits you like lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.17,0:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you're feeling perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, there's an excruciating pain in your leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like somebody just stuck a sword right through your shin bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.48,0:13:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you fall to the ground from the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.89,0:13:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to carry gout medicine around with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.12,0:13:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, the heart was doing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.54,0:13:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of other peculiar things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the gastrointestinal tract was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.85,0:13:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,threatening to perforate over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.52,0:13:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the duodenal ulcer would reoccur in different places.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.12,0:13:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it started to burrow into the pancreas, into the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.76,0:13:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.61,0:13:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, well, I have to do a subtotal gastrectomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.07,0:13:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, I don't think I'll have that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.98,0:14:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, then I landed in the hospital with diverticulitis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.62,0:14:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hemorrhagic diverticulitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.25,0:14:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I had to have transfusions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,three or four bottles of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.75,0:14:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I really bled a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would land in the hospital for a transfusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of hemorrhagic diverticulitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.41,0:14:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And how it got a chance with the ulcer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to hold the main attention, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it would manage to do that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And farther down the gastrointestinal tract,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,other problems arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.03,0:14:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was like a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The gastrointestinal tract, the acute pancreatitis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.13,0:14:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I had that at one time, diverticulitis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.03,0:14:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hemorrhaging, and you're dying of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't do anything about all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.37,0:14:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.50,0:14:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where I am today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.95,0:14:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't advise lots of people in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to try what I tried, but.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the power of spirit, and prayer, and healing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrendering to God, and all these things disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, a lot of other illnesses I've forgotten about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.74,0:15:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there were so many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.91,0:15:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like 27 active diseases at one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.86,0:15:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.13,0:15:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I've forgotten half of the other ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.58,0:15:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Half of the rest of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.75,0:15:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they all served some karmic for,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.13,0:15:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they all served some karmic, karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.52,0:15:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They all served a karmic benefit, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.30,0:15:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They all served a karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.76,0:15:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you think you're losing, and you're winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're paying off the credit bureau every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.75,0:15:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking, you still owe $5,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.67,0:15:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But you forget, you once owned $42,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:16:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're down to $5,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.12,0:16:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these things heal themselves one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.12,0:16:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, there's so many of them that I forget them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.10,0:16:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, illness can serve some karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, unconscious guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the course of miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.82,0:16:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and according to my own understanding, unconscious guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,does play a role.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.03,0:16:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever I get wrong with myself throughout the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I would forgive myself and repent
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.82,0:16:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for having done that to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry that I have caused others
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.82,0:16:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to lose great quantities of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.37,0:16:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you about the surgery I had in the hernia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.46,0:16:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, I wasn't able to go surrender faster than the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,With the amputation, I was lifted into a beatific state.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.46,0:16:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,With the hernia repair, I was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.32,0:16:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.27,0:16:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was counting on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:17:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in the middle of it, the pain was excruciating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was severe, like bad, bad, bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.63,0:17:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the nurse had to grit her teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.95,0:17:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, I never saw anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.54,0:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the nurse kept me going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.69,0:17:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept looking in my eyes, and her spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.21,0:17:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was holding my spirit's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.56,0:17:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Got through surgery without anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.60,0:17:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you, in the middle of that surgery, the question was,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,why God?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't work like it always worked in other situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering to the pain and thereby eliminating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.92,0:17:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when I remembered putting the spear right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,through that warrior's groin and leaving him to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.92,0:17:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.05,0:17:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't, see, the honor of one warrior to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.38,0:17:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have left him one bullet in his revolver.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.36,0:17:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In those days, we only had spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.02,0:17:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I speared him right through the groin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I lacked the temerity to finish him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.44,0:18:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And that bothered me for some, many a lifetime, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I had two or three hernia repairs in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.51,0:18:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I had three of them, come to think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.27,0:18:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.14,0:18:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And right in the middle of it, I remembered my guilt that I had not
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.01,0:18:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,granted him the favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.18,0:18:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.05,0:18:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Of allowing him to die quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.74,0:18:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in those days, to die of a wound took weeks of agony and fever
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally convulsing and you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.14,0:18:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I undid that karmic debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.05,0:18:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So not healing, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't feel that it's a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.90,0:18:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look inside yourself and say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.27,0:18:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what this is compensating for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.22,0:18:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I surrender it to thee, O Lord, that it may serve the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can surrender your illnesses to serve the highest good in what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,way you may not remember individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.98,0:19:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have also collectively accumulated some negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.92,0:19:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,While one man stands and shoots another's,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.09,0:19:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the six who stand on the sidewalk and cheer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are joining into his karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.66,0:19:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you agree with, you join with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.53,0:19:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which you agree with, you join with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.03,0:19:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.11,0:19:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you agree with, you join with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the bystander who eggs people on thinks they're a scammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're escaping the karmic consequences, but they are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.98,0:19:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when they come back, you see whole ethnic groups wiped out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,whole sections of the country wiped out, tsunamis wiping out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think all these people are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they all came around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.19,0:19:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They all went into agreement about such and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.36,0:19:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all now have collectively the karmic debt of undoing that agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:20:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You think of the Goths and the Vikings and the Visigoths.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.77,0:20:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the people that used to swarm and then killed everybody, killed all the innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.85,0:20:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,killed the children, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the karmic consequence of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.81,0:20:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you come back to Hiroshima or some other place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.24,0:20:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what makes sense to me, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not be the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, it probably is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the way it is, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the way it is, collective karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.40,0:20:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see big group phenomena, and people think, look at all those innocents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.90,0:20:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they were not all innocents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of karmic propensity, they just happened to be there as a part of that group to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.57,0:20:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,out the disasters that they had visited upon others, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.31,0:20:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see that slide again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough of my own sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.52,0:21:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.91,0:21:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to bring up healing versus treating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.09,0:21:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be coming up at this medical conference we'll have on October.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.40,0:21:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interesting, treating and healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What the average doctor does is treat, and what's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.02,0:21:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor-doctor, a doctor-doctor calibrates probably, is practicing medicine at about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.35,0:21:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,440, 445.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.48,0:21:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.68,0:21:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,445.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The average academically trained doctor is practicing at a consciousness level of about 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.08,0:21:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, and he usually sticks to academically approved things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.63,0:21:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always looking for approval and approval of his peers and looking for scientific evidence, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.38,0:21:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The healer comes from a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.44,0:22:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. The healer would be probably 450, 460, 470, 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The healer is coming from 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.13,0:22:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 440 to 465 is a big difference, big difference, because these are logarithmic numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.80,0:22:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So 465 is a far more powerful healing field than that below it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.78,0:22:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the academic medical practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.27,0:22:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there is the healer, who is usually holistic and willing to do anything to help a patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.75,0:22:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember having to make that decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.72,0:22:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this patient sitting in front of me in the office, desperately ill, seeing everybody in the world and hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.33,0:22:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to make a decision then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.04,0:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I going to stick to academic medicine and gain the approval of my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.54,0:22:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.84,0:23:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was I going to try non-traditional healing techniques and lose their approval?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.96,0:23:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, on this bed, I am answerable to God for this patient, this soul lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.44,0:23:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's given to me to heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.34,0:23:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I made that decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.00,0:23:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I used everything that would possibly be beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.39,0:23:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Acupuncture and all kinds of health techniques and rotation diets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.25,0:23:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember, I think I told you about the patient who was sitting there, he was schizophrenic as all get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd seen everybody in the world, came from a very rich family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.44,0:23:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We treated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.14,0:23:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a low-cost clinic, but we treated a lot of wealthy people because they had been everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd fly him in from Paris or wherever, in Uganda, God knows where.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.96,0:24:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And as he's sitting there talking to me, in the back of my mind, he's hopeless schizophrenic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.36,0:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All the antipsychotics have been tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.63,0:24:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And as he's talking on, I'm thinking to myself, not thinking to myself, but the thought comes into me, he's as mad as a hatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.68,0:24:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He was as mad as a hatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.42,0:24:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in the old days, hatters would lick a brush and get mercury and get mercury poisoning and become crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.16,0:24:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And old hatters were rather routinely quite crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.93,0:24:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, he's mad as a hatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.75,0:24:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.39,0:24:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, we'll get a hair test and test it for trace metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.52,0:24:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.65,0:24:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So he turned out to have all kinds of mercury in his brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.96,0:24:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, he was allergic to wheat, and I did rotation diets and acupuncture.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.33,0:24:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I did all the things that traditional medicine pooh-poohs is ridiculous, and he recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.20,0:24:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was routine at that clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.38,0:24:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, that's why we had such a huge clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.66,0:25:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We had 2,000 outpatients and 1,000 new ones a year and a staff of 50 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.48,0:25:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had a huge library.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.20,0:25:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I had all kinds of laboratories and 50 people working for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.79,0:25:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was only the difference between treating and healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.11,0:25:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd all been in treatment, but as yet, they weren't healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.01,0:25:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intention of the healer, then, as you see by the Heisenberg principle, the intention of the healer has a profound effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.10,0:25:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So two doctors with the same kind of a patient and similar kinds of treatments will get two different kinds of results.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.96,0:25:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.16,0:25:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the energy field of the physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.67,0:25:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're not getting well, look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.24,0:25:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My intention is, and I'm going to give my all, that this patient is going to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.29,0:25:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By God, you're going to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.13,0:26:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to recover whether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.54,0:26:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, even after I retired and came out here, I treated lots of hopeless patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.88,0:26:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.66,0:26:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've told you about a lot of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.03,0:26:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy with the oxygen tank, and he asked me to light a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.51,0:26:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, do you do that at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.11,0:26:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.74,0:26:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.31,0:26:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.83,0:26:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I lit a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.64,0:26:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't blow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.74,0:26:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.28,0:26:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He said we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.23,0:26:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.81,0:26:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.92,0:26:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the contribution of the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.75,0:26:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.98,0:26:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we haven't talked about intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.74,0:26:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody has, you know, researched this yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.05,0:26:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one, if I was 10 years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.75,0:26:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.01,0:26:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you know, the Heisenberg principle is to merely observe a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.98,0:26:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To observe an experiment already changes the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.16,0:27:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you can't do the same experiment twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.86,0:27:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the first time, having looked at it, you've already changed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.17,0:27:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't put your foot in the same river twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.24,0:27:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle, then, nobody has ever researched.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.34,0:27:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.06,0:27:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find out the answers ourselves without bothering with all that research and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.70,0:27:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.48,0:27:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.11,0:27:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more powerful the level of consciousness of the witness observer,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.90,0:27:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the more powerful the effect is going to be on the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.59,0:27:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.59,0:27:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person who is not to evolve will witness a phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.03,0:27:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring about very little change.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.61,0:27:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little change.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.79,0:27:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little change.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.81,0:27:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little change.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.83,0:27:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the energy field of humanness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.25,0:27:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But a person of a much higher level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.92,0:27:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to have a very powerful effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.59,0:28:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So via the Heisenberg principle, then, the healer, from a scientific viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.27,0:28:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would statistically have better results rather regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.72,0:28:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because of who they are and the power of their intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.35,0:28:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So a doctor who calibrates at 540 once you get well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.68,0:28:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to have a higher recovery rate than a doctor who calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.79,0:28:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So a doctor who calibrates at 205 is really an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.64,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's the first thing I'd ask a doctor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an atheist?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.41,0:28:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a free country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.54,0:28:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.85,0:28:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.00,0:28:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not objecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.90,0:28:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to offend the left wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.64,0:28:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, no, you're perfectly fine to be an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.48,0:28:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, the power of intention, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.88,0:28:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.11,0:28:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.24,0:28:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.20,0:28:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people, if they hold the thing in mind, it's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.05,0:29:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people, for karmic reasons as well, it's not likely going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.90,0:29:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know every place I've lived in for the last 40 years or 50 years or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.48,0:29:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely envisioned the kind of place that I would really like to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.90,0:29:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.38,0:29:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing that I knew, it would appear out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.00,0:29:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody would call me and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.22,0:29:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the house next door is for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.96,0:29:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hold in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.98,0:29:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.03,0:29:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you hold in mind what you don't want,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.31,0:29:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit doesn't get the don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.92,0:29:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It just gets tumbled down brick shack, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.77,0:29:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's his.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.35,0:29:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What you've been holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.42,0:29:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, you hold in mind what you do want and not what you don't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.57,0:29:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.95,0:29:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the difference between healing and treating.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.39,0:29:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And we talked about non-healing as a benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.84,0:29:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.36,0:30:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, the power of faith and belief to a group like this is, of course, starkly obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.13,0:30:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, do we have one more slide on this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.71,0:30:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.49,0:30:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.73,0:30:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What prevents the miraculous from happening or seemingly prevents it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.45,0:30:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, people below 200 do not experience miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.39,0:30:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.32,0:30:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,People below 200 do not experience miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.99,0:30:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder they're skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.70,0:30:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't blame them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.76,0:30:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that brings up lack of karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.11,0:30:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All it takes is like Constantine did.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.81,0:30:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantine calibrated at 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.16,0:30:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a great emperor on his own at 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.73,0:30:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But the minute he began to search for God, search for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.93,0:31:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and if there is a God, I ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.32,0:31:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ask for a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.41,0:31:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask for a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.63,0:31:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He instantly went up to 250 or 245, whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.41,0:31:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the person who experienced the miracle looked up at the sky and saw that sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.02,0:31:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't calibrate at 190, calibrated at 250, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.78,0:31:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,245.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.65,0:31:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, intention can change the conditions and the likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I think prayer is a very powerful tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.77,0:31:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not causal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.27,0:31:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again, the skeptic will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.35,0:31:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,well, look at millions of people pray for something or other and it doesn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.74,0:31:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he negates the power of prayer because he's looking at it as cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.72,0:31:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.94,0:31:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to my slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.53,0:31:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a dollar for the slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.60,0:31:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just talking about the blocks, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.13,0:32:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.84,0:32:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you haven't paid off enough to have gotten to the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.95,0:32:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's much of a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.57,0:32:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lack of willingness to surrender secondary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.55,0:32:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how we punish other people with our suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.42,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look how I suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.91,0:32:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how I suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.77,0:32:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of willingness to surrender secondary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.70,0:32:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all the advantages you get from having problems and difficulties and being sick and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.21,0:32:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the secondary gain of hating people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.84,0:32:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what could be more fun than hating people?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.42,0:32:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night on television you see it, there's always a crowd protesting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.77,0:32:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Protesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.14,0:32:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Exhibiting hate and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.98,0:32:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.22,0:32:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing rocks at the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.81,0:32:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, provoking the police into action so you can make the police wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.48,0:32:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, just as the policeman says,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.55,0:33:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,stop, you go like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.40,0:33:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he shoots you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.09,0:33:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to wait until he gets shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.79,0:33:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, one of you is going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.74,0:33:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God was trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.11,0:33:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we do is we try.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.27,0:33:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to trick, trick that which is legitimate into looking at that which is illegitimate so we can have the good fun of, uh, hating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.43,0:33:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the lack of willingness to surrender the secondary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.43,0:33:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The secondary gain, the most common one, is being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.44,0:33:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest in today's world is a moral one of who, who is the most moral you can watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.40,0:33:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single thing that's on television is struggling
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.64,0:33:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to be moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.74,0:33:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To be morally superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.09,0:33:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the morally right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.09,0:33:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single story is a struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.65,0:33:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who has the moral high ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.65,0:33:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,End the struggle for moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.05,0:33:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all, all it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.05,0:33:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Take any story that's out in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.38,0:34:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the struggle for the moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.38,0:34:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral high ground is I'm justified in doing this, or the troops are justified in doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.96,0:34:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so the moral high ground gives you justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.76,0:34:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the justification, justification to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.07,0:34:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the what that comes up next.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.44,0:34:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, politics is really the struggle over moral, uh, superiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.50,0:34:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is right and who has the, and who should feel guilty, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.23,0:34:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Lack of willingness to surrender the secondary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.23,0:34:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, truth, as you can see, becomes inconsequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.23,0:34:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is inconsequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.42,0:34:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's who is holding the moral high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.42,0:34:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.42,0:34:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who, it's not who wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.42,0:34:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's who looks the goodest on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.42,0:34:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, image is what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.42,0:34:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.82,0:34:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Image is what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.82,0:35:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's so much gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.86,0:35:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego juice, we say the way to get off, get unhooked from anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.86,0:35:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll probably do a whole lecture on getting unhooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.86,0:35:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is, uh, the willingness to let go of the gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.92,0:35:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First to find out what is the juice you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.92,0:35:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then ask yourself if you're willing to let go of the secondary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.92,0:35:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The satisfaction, the grim satisfaction, usually of being right, of watching other
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.92,0:35:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,people suffer, and hitting them over the head with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.30,0:35:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, guilt is the weapon that's used today.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.69,0:35:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It, this is the international game.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.69,0:35:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you were wrong in blowing up them, and they were wrong, we were right in blowing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.69,0:35:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,up them, because they blew up us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.69,0:35:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you run out of current events, you can go back 400 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.69,0:35:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 400 years ago, when they invaded so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.69,0:35:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you run out of something current, history is full of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.75,0:35:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Blacks versus whites, women versus men, you name the political conflict in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.75,0:36:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you can always go back into history and justify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.88,0:36:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, why we should hate somebody or not hate somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.88,0:36:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, so there's no, no, uh, deficit of reasons that justify hatred and, uh, thereby guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.55,0:36:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these resentments are then called, uh, justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.55,0:36:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, one of the first things we learn in a 12-step group is there are no justified resentments.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.55,0:36:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.55,0:36:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not joining that group.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.67,0:36:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,After all my mother did to me, and after, uh, my first wife did, and, uh, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.67,0:36:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, people, um, suck that guy for years and years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.09,0:36:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen people who carry, you know, resentments 60, 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.09,0:36:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,80 years old, and they still got a resentment against their little sister or their mother or a neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.21,0:36:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God knows what.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.42,0:36:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't seem to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.90,0:37:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the willingness to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.90,0:37:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you need a miracle, what you ask for is a miracle to see how you can surrender that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.90,0:37:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's causing you so much pain and disrupting the life of everybody around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.96,0:37:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The miracle you could ask for is then, ask the old Lord to show me how I can let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.30,0:37:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Being hooked on the gain I'm getting from this resentment, from this self-pity, from this fear, from this anger, from this self-hatred, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.84,0:37:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the miracle you want is internal.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.84,0:37:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not trying to change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.84,0:37:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't pray for the miracle that one side should win or the other side not win.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.84,0:37:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you pray for the miracle that you can, that your ego is willing to surrender to God's will in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.84,0:37:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.05,0:37:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.05,0:37:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.05,0:37:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then there comes like a new way of looking at it and a new way of looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.28,0:38:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I like something it says in the fifth chapter in the AA book that people can't help being the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.28,0:38:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instead of resenting them or hating them, there are people who are born that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.38,0:38:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.38,0:38:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be born that way and they don't seem to be able to do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.92,0:38:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a neat way of putting it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.92,0:38:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates or Jesus Christ's admonition into practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.92,0:38:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said, forgive them for they know not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.34,0:38:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, Christians have had a hard time applying that over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.30,0:38:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore, I was telling them to get around that one because everybody's got a resentment that Jesus put them on the spot by saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.61,0:38:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody got a resentment about Jesus for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.46,0:38:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I always had a resentment about Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.13,0:39:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I always had a resentment about that because he made you feel guilty that you, you know, were angry or resentful about somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.13,0:39:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be forgiving him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.13,0:39:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you forgive him when he just ran over your favorite toy?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.13,0:39:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.13,0:39:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Squashed it with his bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.34,0:39:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm trying to forgive him for wrecking my toy with his bicycle because Jesus said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.34,0:39:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But I finally couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.34,0:39:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I still was mad at the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.38,0:39:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now you got two problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.38,0:39:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One, you're mad at the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.38,0:39:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, you feel guilty because you're mad at the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.38,0:39:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I used to go for religious counseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.76,0:39:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They called it, what did they call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.76,0:39:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.76,0:39:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you want to get over the justified resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.28,0:39:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the juice you're willing to, that you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you try to surrender to the karma of the other person who probably is completely unable to be any different they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.28,0:39:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.28,0:39:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they were able to be different than what they are, they would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.28,0:40:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is only what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.92,0:40:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the stunning reality that everyone is being exactly what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.01,0:40:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they could be some other way, they would be, answers the whole problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.01,0:40:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They're full of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.61,0:40:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If they could be forgiving, they would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.61,0:40:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, they can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.61,0:40:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have all generations in parts of the world now that are being brainwashed and trained in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.73,0:40:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Being brainwashed and trained into hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.73,0:40:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We see them on Dennis, whatchamacallit's program.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.90,0:40:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Little children getting out there and they've been indoctrinated with hate at age five or six.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.90,0:40:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's shouting all these slogans of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.90,0:40:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the justified resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.38,0:40:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as a justified resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.38,0:40:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the resentment is only because of the way you're seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.38,0:40:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I agree with the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.38,0:40:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They re-contextualize it differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.38,0:40:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're automatically released.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.38,0:41:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that people cannot help being what they are at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.38,0:41:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, they could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.42,0:41:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.42,0:41:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical is always fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.42,0:41:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical is always fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.57,0:41:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.57,0:41:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it count very below 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.57,0:41:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.57,0:41:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fantasy that you use to project onto other people as a make wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.57,0:41:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they could be different than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.57,0:41:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If they could be, they would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.11,0:41:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anybody see the reality of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.11,0:41:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be, you would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.11,0:41:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You would automatically be that which you could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.17,0:41:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be that, you would be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.17,0:41:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.25,0:41:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.30,0:41:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People can't be different than what they are, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.30,0:41:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, justified resentments, we let them go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.69,0:41:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to control others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.26,0:41:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to control others is a difficult one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.26,0:41:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know if it's possible within the human domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.26,0:41:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.55,0:42:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible to do it in major areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.55,0:42:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But in small areas, it's almost like ubiquitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.55,0:42:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like inherent.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.55,0:42:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Demands animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.55,0:42:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like because of our biologic origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.90,0:42:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we have preferences and we have frictions with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.90,0:42:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire to control is very difficult to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.34,0:42:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.34,0:42:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of our biologic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.34,0:42:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.34,0:42:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we trace the emergence of consciousness and life on this planet from the beginning of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.34,0:42:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that the bacteria has to get energy elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.63,0:42:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not full of chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.63,0:42:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's got to have energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.86,0:42:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the protozoa, the amoeba, the smallest early forms of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.86,0:42:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be able to detect what's out there so they can take it into itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.86,0:43:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't have chlorophyll to create energy out of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.86,0:43:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So all biologic life has to seek and find,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.88,0:43:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be able to sample what's out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.88,0:43:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,see if it's digestible, if it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.88,0:43:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that, they would...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.94,0:43:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Life would stop because you'd fail energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.69,0:43:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind is always searching out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.67,0:43:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And we call that the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.67,0:43:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of the ego is sampling everything around you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.67,0:43:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and savoring,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.67,0:43:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's good for your survival or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.67,0:43:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's instinctual.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.67,0:43:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to control is basic to the existence of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.92,0:43:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's intrinsic, inborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.34,0:43:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.65,0:43:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You've either got to eat this or spit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.65,0:43:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either poison or it's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.65,0:43:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.55,0:43:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the desire to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.94,0:43:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when you begin to see its forms of expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.94,0:44:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that what you're looking for in other people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.09,0:44:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is to have your own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.09,0:44:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.09,0:44:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to detect the narcissistic core of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.09,0:44:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you can let go of.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.09,0:44:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to control in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.09,0:44:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.09,0:44:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.09,0:44:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the desire to control,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.19,0:44:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't get too far in the highway, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.19,0:44:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the steering wheel and the brake are for.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.19,0:44:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.19,0:44:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,One form a desire to control takes is, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.09,0:44:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,outlining.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.09,0:44:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Outlining is a technical term,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.09,0:44:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning telling God how you want things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.09,0:44:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want her to get married and then have three children,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.25,0:44:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.25,0:44:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to do this and the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.25,0:44:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're telling God,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.25,0:44:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, please let my sister-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.25,0:44:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,move out of this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.30,0:45:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling God how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.30,0:45:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.30,0:45:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of praying to God is really manipulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.69,0:45:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking you can use divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.69,0:45:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and entreaty through prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.69,0:45:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, please let me so.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.69,0:45:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you're not asking for revelation and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.01,0:45:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So Constantine was asking for revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.01,0:45:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He was praying to God for some kind of a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.34,0:45:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.34,0:45:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me win over my brother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.34,0:45:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.34,0:45:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me be the sole emperor of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.34,0:45:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.65,0:45:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for some kind of a sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.03,0:45:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of a signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.03,0:45:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,something of a significance
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.03,0:45:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to affirm his faith and his belief.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.03,0:45:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it manifested
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.03,0:45:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and changed all of.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.03,0:45:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn't tell God what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.03,0:45:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He pleaded with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.03,0:45:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we've calibrated here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.38,0:46:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,those who acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.82,0:46:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.78,0:46:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and devote themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.36,0:46:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.42,0:46:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,their prayers cannot be refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.28,0:46:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean they will be answered in the way you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.28,0:46:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but they will be heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.28,0:46:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who turn their life over to God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.28,0:46:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.28,0:46:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,saith the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.28,0:46:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,91st Psalm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.32,0:46:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna says the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.32,0:46:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who worship me
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.57,0:46:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.78,0:46:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.78,0:46:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who acknowledge God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.28,0:46:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and worship God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.28,0:46:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and willing to accept God's will in all matters
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.28,0:46:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,belong to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.28,0:46:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,saith the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.63,0:46:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.63,0:46:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God says you belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.63,0:46:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.69,0:46:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're speaking to God now,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.69,0:46:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking to him
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.69,0:46:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as one who belongs to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.69,0:46:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So God's answer then
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.69,0:47:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is in whatever is going to serve the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.69,0:47:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever is going to serve the highest good
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.69,0:47:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,may not be
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.69,0:47:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you would like it to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.69,0:47:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that is not going to serve your highest good
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.69,0:47:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not going to serve your
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.69,0:47:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest long-term happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.69,0:47:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because sometimes to go down the wrong road
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.69,0:47:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only way you can learn
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.69,0:47:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not to go down that road anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.67,0:47:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Overcoming negative karma
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.38,0:47:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,means a willingness to accept responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.38,0:47:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and to face it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.38,0:47:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.38,0:47:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the habit I had over the years was
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.38,0:47:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that happened untoward in my environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.38,0:47:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I took responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.38,0:47:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for being
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.38,0:47:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a part of the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.57,0:47:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,source of that phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.96,0:47:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.28,0:47:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if I
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.90,0:47:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,bled to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.90,0:47:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,bled from something,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.90,0:47:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.90,0:47:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,pray for forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.65,0:47:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the one in me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.65,0:48:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who cut somebody else's jugular vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.65,0:48:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.00,0:48:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm sure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.00,0:48:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't have lived all these lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.00,0:48:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world the way it was
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.00,0:48:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in barbarian days
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.00,0:48:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and not have cut somebody's throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.00,0:48:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't no way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.00,0:48:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that you could have survived very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.00,0:48:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You pretty much got to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.00,0:48:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hack somebody to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.00,0:48:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're not,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.00,0:48:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then the captain behind you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.00,0:48:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will put you to death
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.00,0:48:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for being a bad soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.00,0:48:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.00,0:48:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.82,0:48:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.82,0:48:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we may not take on,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.17,0:48:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we take on
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.17,0:48:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.17,0:48:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but not culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.17,0:48:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's an important point.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.17,0:48:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.25,0:48:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,vis-a-vis culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.25,0:48:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be karmically responsible,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.44,0:48:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that means accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.44,0:48:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're accountable if you did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.32,0:48:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability means degree of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.32,0:48:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,moral responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.32,0:48:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.32,0:48:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have done it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.63,0:49:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but done it innocently.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.63,0:49:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have accountability,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.63,0:49:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you owe that life that you took,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.63,0:49:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may not have culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.57,0:49:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No one will necessarily have to suffer for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.57,0:49:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.98,0:49:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you could do a thing out of,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.98,0:49:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.98,0:49:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,wickedness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.98,0:49:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems minor
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.26,0:49:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have much to undo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.94,0:49:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're accountable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.07,0:49:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.07,0:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're accountable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.07,0:49:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're culpable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.07,0:49:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So culpable is degree of guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.07,0:49:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.07,0:49:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the courts,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.07,0:49:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that's,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.57,0:49:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,even courts recognize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.57,0:49:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.57,0:49:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no question that the person did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.57,0:49:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But what was his motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.57,0:49:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.57,0:49:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,not only do things happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.57,0:49:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but they happen in different circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.57,0:49:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with different degrees of motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.57,0:49:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking on full personal motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.94,0:49:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're taking on full culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.34,0:49:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Full culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.34,0:49:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as accountability.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.34,0:50:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.63,0:50:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the things that go on in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.63,0:50:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what the people believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.63,0:50:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.21,0:50:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're accountable for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.21,0:50:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the way in which they do it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.17,0:50:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,changes the degree of culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.46,0:50:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it volitional?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.46,0:50:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they just brainwashed?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.46,0:50:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.46,0:50:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Unwilling to,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.19,0:50:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to do negative karma then.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.19,0:50:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you've done the best you can
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.19,0:50:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.19,0:50:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and you still are stuck with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.19,0:50:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you just surrender it to God and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.19,0:50:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that must be coming from some place
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.78,0:50:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I accept my responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.78,0:50:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo that for the benefit of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.78,0:50:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,myself and perhaps others.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.84,0:50:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I think some people take on
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.84,0:50:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,other people's negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.84,0:50:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if they do it willingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.84,0:50:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people will take on
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.00,0:50:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,other people's negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.00,0:50:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingly resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.00,0:50:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.00,0:51:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.34,0:51:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't know the reason then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.05,0:51:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Overblown emotionality and hysteria
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.96,0:51:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is another problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.96,0:51:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad enough
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.96,0:51:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you lose a body part
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.96,0:51:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or your car gets crashed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.25,0:51:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or your child marries a horrible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.32,0:51:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But going into hysterics about it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.32,0:51:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is a whole different phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.46,0:51:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of times
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.46,0:51:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see people praying up a storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.46,0:51:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what they're really doing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.78,0:51:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is reacting to the hysteria
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.78,0:51:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.78,0:51:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The hysteria of the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.78,0:51:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The hysteria of the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.21,0:51:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous can occur
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.80,0:51:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in very profound ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.13,0:51:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watch the History Channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.13,0:51:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see the miraculous frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost every survivor
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.13,0:51:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of giant tornadoes and hurricanes and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.13,0:52:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're being interviewed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.13,0:52:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Weather Channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.13,0:52:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you that they prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.73,0:52:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And an interesting one that recurs
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.73,0:52:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively, not infrequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.73,0:52:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the middle of a hurricane,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.96,0:52:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or no, a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.96,0:52:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of a tornado,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.80,0:52:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is lifted high up into the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.09,0:52:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the eye of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.09,0:52:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in the middle of the worst of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.09,0:52:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the first one that said this,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.21,0:52:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I calibrated it at the event at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.21,0:52:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.40,0:52:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with the whole everything being torn to pieces,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.40,0:52:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,she was lifted up in the air about 40 feet
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.40,0:52:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.69,0:52:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And suspended like in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.69,0:52:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspended by the hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.69,0:52:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And went into a state of infinite profound peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.69,0:52:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as I had in the snow bank as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.69,0:52:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.69,0:53:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the world flying around in pieces,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.69,0:53:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,people dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.75,0:53:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've heard that more than once.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.36,0:53:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.36,0:53:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.36,0:53:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.36,0:53:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.36,0:53:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll see God,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.36,0:53:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.36,0:53:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God's opportunity is your spirit's,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.36,0:53:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.36,0:53:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your calamity is God's opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.38,0:53:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll notice that you watch the weather channel,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.94,0:53:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,one after another,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.94,0:53:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it says I really prayed up a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.94,0:53:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them that survives,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.94,0:53:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about 90%,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.00,0:53:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,well spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.00,0:53:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not questioning about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.00,0:53:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they say I prayed up a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.00,0:53:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And every once in a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.28,0:53:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about twice a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.28,0:53:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see somebody suspended in the middle of the storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.28,0:53:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and went into a state of profound peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.34,0:53:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And went into a state of profound and infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.34,0:53:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.34,0:53:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.34,0:53:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got your choice in the middle of a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.34,0:53:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can panic and,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.34,0:53:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and scream,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.40,0:53:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can just surrender to the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.40,0:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and go into a state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.40,0:54:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's option.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.76,0:54:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That option is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.76,0:54:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Complete surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.36,0:54:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.09,0:54:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.63,0:54:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How about your signal light?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.63,0:54:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were going to turn on your signal light.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.63,0:54:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See the signal light.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.82,0:54:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.53,0:54:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.53,0:54:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.88,0:54:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.88,0:54:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is a wonderful place for research.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.88,0:54:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And people exchanging,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.88,0:54:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.88,0:54:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and miracles groups and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.88,0:54:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to do so well,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.88,0:54:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you like share that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.88,0:54:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And what seems like a potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.88,0:54:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.88,0:54:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People all begin to exchange experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.88,0:54:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.88,0:54:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I am getting a signal
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.88,0:54:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from one of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.88,0:54:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm talking to right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.88,0:54:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.88,0:54:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.88,0:54:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.88,0:54:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.88,0:54:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.88,0:54:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.88,0:54:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.88,0:54:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.94,0:54:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.94,0:54:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.94,0:54:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.94,0:54:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.94,0:54:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.07,0:54:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting a signal
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.07,0:54:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.28,0:54:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is my space signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.28,0:54:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.28,0:55:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,she does assembly like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.65,0:55:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll meet again at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.65,0:55:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll meet again at 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.09,0:55:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.09,0:55:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That looks just terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.09,0:55:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that little thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.69,0:55:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.69,0:55:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.69,0:55:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.69,0:55:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned another secret
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.69,0:55:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of human life,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.94,0:55:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.94,0:55:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Women are more non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.61,0:55:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,than men.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.61,0:55:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a great
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.61,0:55:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.65,0:55:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.71,0:55:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.71,0:55:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.71,0:55:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.38,0:56:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery? Women are more non-linear than men. Understanding that will increase compatibility
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.78,0:56:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,between the sexes. That does explain a lot of things. A woman has more tendency to read
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.01,0:56:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the field and the man has more tendency to read the content of the field. They call it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.15,0:56:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,intuition. It doesn't apply to driving, though. That's the serious part of the program. Now
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.80,0:57:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll get to the light-hearted one. I thought I'd ring up dying. Is that okay? Well, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.15,0:57:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry. See, everybody, there's various levels of consciousness in which dying means different
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.86,0:57:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,things, of course. If you think you're only a physical being, you're afraid you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.59,0:57:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to expire, etc. But the process of dying itself, if we recontextualize it, you'll see that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.09,0:57:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody's really afraid of it. What you're afraid of on multiple levels, there's multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.42,0:57:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,things you're afraid of with dying. That's a whole lecture in itself. But losing control
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.11,0:57:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.57,0:57:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you're really afraid of is being alone. Now, when you think about this, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.57,0:57:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,see it's so. You picture yourself dying, and what's the tragedy? Everybody else is still
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.63,0:58:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,living. It isn't dying, it's being separated. All right. So now we're facing a possible
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.28,0:58:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,cataclysmic catastrophe, atomic, courtesy of the president of Iran or somebody, who
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.51,0:58:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will bring in the next imam.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.44,0:58:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our expense? The next Mahdi, the next Mahdi. The 12th imam, when he expires, will bring
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.53,0:58:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Mahdi. And it will be apocalyptic. And he believes that as a fact. Okay. So that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.15,0:58:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,means that, you know, unless you just don't watch the news at all, that there is a possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.73,0:58:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we may all be leaving. Who knows? Now, look at this. If we all leave together, all of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.69,0:58:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,us, is there any problem? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.26,0:58:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If the atomic bomb just blows me out and leaves you all here, I'm going to feel poor about
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.13,0:59:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.21,0:59:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we all stay here together, and we all, as I said in previous lectures, this group
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.88,0:59:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to swoop in like birds. You know, they swoop in at a certain time and then they swoop
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.69,0:59:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,out. This whole group has swept in and out of human existence a number of times. And
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.32,0:59:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do research, you can get the details of it. But it's not. It's not. It's not. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.86,0:59:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.86,0:59:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.86,0:59:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that's important. But if we all go together, there's no problem. Let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.65,0:59:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I give you a guarantee that at an exact moment we all leave together. Everybody got a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.63,0:59:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem. So it isn't if you're a dying, is it? If you're leaving the familiarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.84,0:59:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the family of mankind, the family, and it's a family matter. So, if we all hang out together,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.57,0:59:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,now we all tend to swoop in.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.84,1:00:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in and swoop out of this planet as a group. Let's see, we checked this out before. This
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.11,1:00:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,group tends to swoop in and swoop out at about the same time. The whole group, we all come
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.40,1:00:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in and we settle here like flamingos. This group tends to sweep into karmic karma, group
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.84,1:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. People say, well, Christianity doesn't believe in karma, but they do. Oh yes, they
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.48,1:00:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,believe. What do you need a savior for? Because you've inherited original sin. You've got
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.09,1:00:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,plenty of karma. Karma being human, you're born in sin, therefore you need a savior.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.01,1:00:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so? So don't tell me you don't believe in karma or Jesus wouldn't have had
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.32,1:00:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to bother. Oh yes, you have destiny that you inherit virtue by virtue of being human, period.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.15,1:01:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, just for one thing, you're protoplasmic and protoplasmic has a very definite time limit
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.73,1:01:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,on it. That which is eternal in the spirit is different. So it's sort of a comforting
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.46,1:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,thought that we all tend to swoop in together and if we all leave in what we view as prematurely,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.13,1:01:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,actually it won't be premature, it will be perfect timing, we'll probably be able to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.53,1:01:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.40,1:01:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We all go together if, you know, certain cataclysmic things happen. So there's no point to worry
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.21,1:01:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about it. Is that okay? We all die together. Everybody for it? Yay! Okay, anybody want
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.40,1:01:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay here after we all leave? Anybody want to hang in? We've all left. Isn't that a strange
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.88,1:01:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,thing when you reconsexualize it, you realize, I don't want to be the only one left here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.71,1:01:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,without everybody here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.71,1:02:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No. So love then, love then brings us together and the mutuality of that field of love is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.21,1:02:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what we don't want to leave, see? You don't want to be left alone on a desert island and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.26,1:02:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the steamship goes away with everybody except you. And we have all these things to accomplish
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.03,1:02:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,while we're here. I've been busy living through all this karma. I told you all the physical
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.80,1:02:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,ailments.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.67,1:02:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forgot, I had some money in my, I can't even remember them all. I forgot breaking
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.55,1:02:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,my back. That was sort of an oozes too. I told you, I lifted something and my back collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.80,1:02:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,three vertebrae collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.84,1:02:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifting a skunk, yes. Well, yes. It was a skunk trap and I lifted the skunk trap and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.71,1:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt this shrieking pain down my back. God. And three vertebrae collapsed, yeah. Osteoporosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.61,1:03:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So you pick up things from the collective. I thought, well, I've never held in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.07,1:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you tend to manifest what you hold in mind. I've never pictured that men get
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.98,1:03:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,osteoporosis. You know, I was pictured little bent old ladies, you know. When I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.92,1:03:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there was all little bent over ladies and they all had severe osteoporosis and kyphosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.51,1:03:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I never thought it assailed men. So it wasn't something I was personally holding
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.78,1:03:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind. So that means we're all a similar subject.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.51,1:03:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To what is being held in the collective consciousness. So instead of berating yourself for some kind
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.71,1:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of negative experience and thinking, boy, I must have bad karma or something, it can
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.44,1:03:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,be something you've picked up from the collective. And that helps you bear some things. So we
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.07,1:04:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,can, we often pick up from the collective and experience it out for the sake of all
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.05,1:04:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of us here at Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.82,1:04:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're all together, you realize when you look into the eyes of anybody, anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.38,1:04:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in the group, if God said to you, would you go through some agony so that she would have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.78,1:04:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to bear less? You would say yes, wouldn't you? You would just automatically sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.23,1:04:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,say yes. Why? Because love knows no boundaries. So for the sake of a loved one, there's no
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.05,1:04:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,higher love than spiritual love. Out of spiritual love, you would. You would, I agree. Yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.59,1:04:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would bear that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.26,1:04:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For that person. And because you're doing it voluntarily, it's willing. So if you allow
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.42,1:04:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,any kind of suffering in your life to be voluntary, you've already eliminated 90% of the suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.96,1:04:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is purely physical. But the suffering is really the mental anguish, isn't it? It's
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.46,1:05:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the anguish. The anguish.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.26,1:05:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I drove myself up, up the road with this busted back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.13,1:05:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.82,1:05:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the anguish that I wasn't going to get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.84,1:05:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know if the body would hang in long enough
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.03,1:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or I might pass out on 89A trying to get to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.09,1:05:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So although the pain was severe,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.15,1:05:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it was really the anguish of your capacity to handle it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.84,1:05:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the situation in which you're in.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.17,1:05:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can look at pain and suffering and death in different ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.03,1:05:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes recontextualized,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.84,1:05:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you say, can you bear the physicality for a period of time?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.30,1:05:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can bear the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.61,1:05:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the anguish that makes it seem unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.90,1:05:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't the pain, it's the anguish,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.73,1:05:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's going to last forever, it's never going to come to an end, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.21,1:06:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When all hope is gone, that's characteristic of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.90,1:06:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the depths of hell, there is no hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.51,1:06:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon all hope, you enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.28,1:06:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You enter here, and you enter agony forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.88,1:06:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.21,1:06:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the agony, although that is severe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.53,1:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the forever, and you begin to experience out what eternity is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.09,1:06:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And eternity is foreverness, and with no hope, with no hope ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.84,1:06:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the agony of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.51,1:06:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is our hope and how we contextualize an experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.73,1:06:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes it either excruciating or bearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.96,1:06:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Excruciating or bearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.32,1:06:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality can be handled.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.36,1:06:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I've explained how to handle the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.03,1:06:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I handle all these things that have ailed me at various times,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.67,1:07:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was constantly not labeling it, and letting go, resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.80,1:07:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantly letting go, resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.07,1:07:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you do that, you get closer and closer to the source of the pain or the discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.07,1:07:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you stop labeling it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.82,1:07:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't call it guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.65,1:07:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't call it gastritis, or migraine, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.28,1:07:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You just let go, resisting the sensation, whatever the sensation is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.11,1:07:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And by constantly letting go, resisting it, you transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.15,1:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You overcome it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.61,1:07:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can bypass it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.80,1:07:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It no longer bothers you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.94,1:07:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you can let go of your fear of death, you can let go of fear of anything, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.55,1:07:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How about your fear of being short?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.21,1:07:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.30,1:07:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sure, I wasn't stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.73,1:08:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But they wouldn't let me on the ball field, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.84,1:08:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The coach would never pass me, and the school doctor would never pass me for participatory sports.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.17,1:08:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.92,1:08:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.46,1:08:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're doing the last 99, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.26,1:08:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is slide number 99.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.05,1:08:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last one, correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.85,1:08:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.05,1:08:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,99?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.28,1:08:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.93,1:08:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You were talking about the blocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.39,1:08:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.84,1:08:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.61,1:08:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that should remove the blocks, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.42,1:08:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you remove the blocks, the way is open for the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.47,1:08:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the miraculous really gets quite strong around level, as I say, around level 560, 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.35,1:08:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous becomes absolutely continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.11,1:08:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is hold the thing in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.73,1:08:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it might...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.64,1:09:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're driving down the road in the old truck, and I think the water pump was falling off.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.76,1:09:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had it wired on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.64,1:09:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why it fell off.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.38,1:09:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.18,1:09:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So to correct it, I needed a pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.69,1:09:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you wouldn't believe in that whole truck with all the crap I had in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.31,1:09:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not find a pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.07,1:09:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said to the guy who was with me, I said, all we need is a pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.76,1:09:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And 20 foot ahead of us on the right-hand side of the highway,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.14,1:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was a pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.18,1:09:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I wore the pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.53,1:09:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They were brand new, never used pair of pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.03,1:09:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of thing was just continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.56,1:09:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when you run out of water, you pull up next to something,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.26,1:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that there's a pump handle behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.61,1:09:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's just miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.72,1:09:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your car breaks down a million miles from nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.81,1:09:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that happened to me a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.44,1:09:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the old truck would break down in strange places.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.44,1:09:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knew I was even there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.64,1:10:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And some old pal from years ago would suddenly drive out of nowhere and come up and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.64,1:10:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, you've broken down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.51,1:10:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You need help?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.43,1:10:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.94,1:10:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I told you one time I was down near the Mexican border.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.96,1:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I first came out, I drove all over the place with my truck,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.85,1:10:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,getting used to the wild, wild west, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.47,1:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Down near the Mexican border.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.34,1:10:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was super hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.85,1:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing in any direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.42,1:10:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.02,1:10:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get down just north of the Mexican border, near Patagonia, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.02,1:10:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's places where, you know, for 50 miles, there's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.06,1:10:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I pulled the truck in someplace, and it died.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.18,1:10:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And smoke shot out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.47,1:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.15,1:10:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a fire under the hood.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.31,1:10:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the fire under the hood on a million miles from nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.55,1:10:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the smoke is going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.14,1:10:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole cab is full of smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.35,1:10:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.63,1:10:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be able to walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.28,1:11:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you wouldn't get more than a quarter of a mile in that heat with no water.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.61,1:11:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I thought, well, you're leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.05,1:11:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sat back and waited to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.97,1:11:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to die sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.25,1:11:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So why not now?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.10,1:11:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm sitting there waiting to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.44,1:11:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay with me to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.09,1:11:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I've been okay to go, it never happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.17,1:11:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What I should do is resist it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.84,1:11:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm not going.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.23,1:11:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I would sit back and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.10,1:11:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you go, so you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.27,1:11:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to be able to walk for water.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.93,1:11:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the machine's on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.39,1:11:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.42,1:11:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a little voice inside my head,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.88,1:11:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't come from elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.50,1:11:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from within.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.96,1:11:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It said, it had a paper cup with about this much coffee in the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.42,1:11:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It said, take this paper cup.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.61,1:11:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the bottom of the glove compartment,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.43,1:11:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's made of heavy-duty cardboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.03,1:12:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, take a screwdriver,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.38,1:12:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and jam it through there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.68,1:12:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I took a screwdriver,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.10,1:12:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and I jammed it through the cardboard in the bottom of the glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.50,1:12:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the knowingness, it wasn't a voice, it was a knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.15,1:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness was to pour that through the hole, which I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.19,1:12:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it went like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.89,1:12:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the electrical fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.27,1:12:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hole was exactly over in the electrical apparatus in my old truck,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.75,1:12:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is still very bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.22,1:12:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years of amateur electrical wiring is a rat's nest.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.35,1:12:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'd never find in there, using the intellect or your brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.88,1:12:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where the fire was coming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.26,1:12:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But there it was exact.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.38,1:12:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was a little disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.85,1:12:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.85,1:12:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that put the fire out.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.34,1:12:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I didn't leave then.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.53,1:12:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Any time I was ready to leave, something similar would happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.53,1:12:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, I've had it happen right in the middle of a lecture, walking down the aisle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.97,1:13:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like invitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.71,1:13:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Level 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.71,1:13:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,From 600 up, it recurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.71,1:13:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like invitational.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.93,1:13:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a very open, welcome door.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.93,1:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have an okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.93,1:13:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got permission to walk through.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.93,1:13:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.25,1:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if the body walks on, I guess that was the karmic momentum to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.51,1:13:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And fulfill your obligation to Doug, to God, that he gave you certain information.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.51,1:13:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like invitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.48,1:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's your obligation to teach others with what you have learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.48,1:13:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you accept that that is to go on and that it's not finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.48,1:13:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what keeps you going.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.48,1:13:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're fulfilling some karmic propensity and even an agreement.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.48,1:13:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember agreement beforehand, in fact, that you're filling a certain contract and obligation
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.48,1:14:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to a group of spirits.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.59,1:14:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say a group of souls.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.81,1:14:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like we all have a certain commitment to each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.00,1:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody ready to die any old time?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.00,1:14:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we ready to go together?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.47,1:14:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, give it the old gung-ho.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.47,1:14:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to go, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.47,1:14:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going to hold everybody else in mind and give it the old college cheer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.47,1:14:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom, off we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.92,1:14:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Fracture of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.92,1:14:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Trumpets sounding on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.92,1:14:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.92,1:14:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.92,1:14:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here comes that wonderful group from Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.92,1:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.92,1:14:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They hang festoons up.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.92,1:14:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're back, they're back, they're back.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.92,1:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy times are here again.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.92,1:14:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.23,1:14:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, inevitably they get tired of the long faces, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.48,1:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They get tired of the sackcloth and ashes type, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.48,1:15:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.68,1:15:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Something to break up the monotony.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.02,1:15:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.02,1:15:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sin and guilt and sackcloth and ashes crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.02,1:15:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.02,1:15:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, sin and guilt and self-recrimination and penance and all that is at the bottom of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.02,1:15:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And joy and happiness is at the top of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.27,1:15:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking God as you wallow around in guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.02,1:15:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so guilt, as Buddhism says, is self-indulgent.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.02,1:15:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is a self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.27,1:15:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, instead of feeling good about thrashing your self.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.27,1:15:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.27,1:15:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling guilt. Shame on you for feeling guilty. So that's guilt. A block to the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.47,1:15:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire to control, we said, has underpinnings. Death itself is probably the most fearsome
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.26,1:16:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of all fears. When you surrender your fear of death, nothing will really frighten you
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.22,1:16:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,after that. The worst that can happen is just so you go, so, so you go, so. And that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.06,1:16:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,attitude that comes up. Once you surrender your fear, so all the negative fears that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.35,1:16:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we have boil down unconsciously to death in one form or another. If you don't live up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.21,1:16:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to certain standards, etc. Disapproval, all these things that would make you, they would
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.93,1:16:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,throw you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.43,1:16:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw you out of the pack. Yeah, throw you out of the pack. So the blocks then are the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.19,1:16:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to control, to resist it. Outlining, we already covered. That's telling God what
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.52,1:16:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you want and why you want it. Advice to God. Advice to God. Sometimes he grants it, he
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.03,1:16:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,feels sorry for you. Throw him a few crumbs because he's going to give up if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.48,1:17:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Unwillingness to undo the negative karma. All right. As we said, Christianity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.93,1:17:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't believe in karma per se as a, as a, as a concept, as a concept. It does believe
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.64,1:17:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in collective human karma, obviously. Adam and Eve and the Garden of Eden and the apple
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.88,1:17:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole story. It's our karmic inheritance. Seeking short-term goals versus long-term
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.64,1:17:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,benefits. Serving the self for the small S instead of the self for the large S. There's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.84,1:17:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not, it's not always possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.52,1:17:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To see what is of the long, most long-term benefit for the self. We say that the relief
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.72,1:17:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of suffering is what the ego wants for now, but we don't know that that serves the highest
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.85,1:17:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,good. So whenever we use kinesiology, we always say in the name of the highest good. Is it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.31,1:18:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,okay to mention this in the name of the highest good? So that is the self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.53,1:18:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinging to the truth we've already described is the basic problem of the self. It's the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.57,1:18:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,problem of the ego. And overblown emotionality is, of course, today's society in which everything
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.46,1:18:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is juiced for its sensationalism. And the media have really brought down the level of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.02,1:18:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. Mm-hmm. Participated. The level of consciousness of America right now
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.46,1:18:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 426, 427, 426. All right. Mankind is currently over 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.10,1:18:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,206. The Mankind, remember, was 207. Yeah. And America was up five more points. So the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.35,1:18:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,collective impact of negativity, the sensationalism of the media, the whole philosophic concept
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.84,1:19:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativism, and Islamic terrorism because it creates fear and anger. You see? So collectively
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.68,1:19:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.56,1:19:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.56,1:19:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the feeling of the mankind is currently down. In fact, you know, here in Sedona, we're
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.35,1:19:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,probably holding it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.35,1:19:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't for this group it would collapse. I'll take it. Now, but this group alone has
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.96,1:19:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a very powerful effect. See? Because we get familiar with each other. We don't realize
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.00,1:19:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the role we're playing. This group, we have permission to ask about it. This group plays
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.35,1:19:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a significant role in the system.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.35,1:19:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.60,1:19:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,upholding the consciousness level of America resists. This group, here, now, because of
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.18,1:20:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the enormous power of spiritual intention, is only helping to hold up. She's catatonic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.15,1:20:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sweetheart. You know, we couldn't do the work without her because, yeah, 20
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.06,1:20:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,times a day I interrupt whatever she's doing, and she looks at me, okay. I had to get Constantine
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.81,1:20:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,before the year 312, and Constantine after 312, and so all those myriad things. Without
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.38,1:20:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology, you realize how much information is shut off from the rest of the world. People
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.17,1:20:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,under 200 can't do it, and those above have to be motivated, and, you know, you have to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.57,1:20:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have at least a minimal amount of skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.80,1:20:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and the difficulty is trying to remain objective, not having a stake in the answer,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.60,1:21:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can find ways in which to remain as objective as possible, and I think asking
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.52,1:21:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good is the best, and sometimes you'll get a no, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.59,1:21:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very serviceable. I mean, how else can you make a diagnosis and design a treatment
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.86,1:21:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for a hopeless condition?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.68,1:21:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was diagnosed with a condition in less than a minute flat for no money at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.36,1:21:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just about everything I had wrong with me, I got the wrong diagnosis. I did. Wrong diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.51,1:21:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I forgot all these illnesses. There were so many of them. Anyway, there was terrible
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.67,1:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,prosthetic problems. All older men are supposed to have prostate problems, and therefore to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.67,1:21:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,go along with being an older man, you have it. And so I see this guy, G.U. man, and I
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.22,1:21:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,went to see him, and he says, oh God, you're going to have to remove it, and fluoroscopy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.52,1:21:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this. He decided, you know, we've got to remove it, and you have to go for surgery.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.52,1:22:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, well, okay, I'll call you. I always get a second opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.07,1:22:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to see another G.U. man, and I sat down, and he was chief of G.U. at the Cottonwood
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.77,1:22:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital, now retired. Anyway, I sat down, and I told him, I said, I don't know, I just
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.69,1:22:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,can't go, and I don't want to go anymore. He says, are you taking anything for your
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.69,1:22:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nose, like Sudafed? I said, yeah. He said, well, stop that, and it'll cure it. I stopped
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.10,1:22:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Sudafed, and it cured it. I always get a second opinion. The doctor that told me
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.80,1:22:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to go home, you're going to die of right-sided heart failure was wrong. It was thyroid. The
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.80,1:22:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,guy who said, you're going to die of right-sided heart failure, he said, you're going to die
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.73,1:22:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of aviary tuberculosis. It's not curable. It's gone. The person who said he had a tumor
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.97,1:23:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the apex of the right lung, it's gone. The person who says, you know, you've got
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.07,1:23:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,atelectasis, it's gone. Pancreatitis is gone. Recurrent duodenal ulcers are gone. I told
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.80,1:23:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you the duodenal ulcer story, intractable, perforating through the, and that would get
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.50,1:23:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it re-X-rayed, and there'd be a new ulcer in a new place. But that was excruciating.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.43,1:23:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's burrowing in the back of the duodenum.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.96,1:23:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was going to die, and I thought I was going to die. And I thought I was going
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.80,1:23:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to die, and I thought I was going to die. But it's still going to die. You know, I
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.38,1:23:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.38,1:23:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I went to the hospital. I went to the doctor, and I saw a medical doctor. A doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.38,1:23:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from the clinic in Washington, D.C. He came into the pancreas, and gave me acute pancreatitis.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.88,1:23:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I heard about acupuncture. Is it something else? Traditional medicine, poo-poos. All
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.39,1:23:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that cure me are all things that medicine poo-poos. Hypoglycemia, acupuncture,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.89,1:23:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things. So, anyway, I heard that there was a Chinese coming from China, and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.65,1:23:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they were going to have the first acupuncture clinic in America, in Washington D.C. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.64,1:23:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went there, you had to get permission and you had to have medical records with you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.89,1:23:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and they took x-rays beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.71,1:23:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw the acupuncturist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.71,1:23:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I told you this story before?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.71,1:23:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.71,1:23:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.71,1:24:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn't speak any English, he had a translator.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.36,1:24:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the first acupuncture clinic in America, it was in DC and it was under federal study.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.44,1:24:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you had to have all the documentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.01,1:24:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I brought all my x-rays of all the ulcers and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.68,1:24:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I laid down and he took all these pins in you and they had moxie combustion,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.51,1:24:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you smell like you're smoking, you know, something illegal, these little puffs of smoke and these
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.82,1:24:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,needles are all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.35,1:24:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he went, he put one right through here, I'll never forget that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.14,1:24:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought acupuncture was painless.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.93,1:24:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he put a needle through here and it came out the back and I screamed and jumped
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.18,1:24:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,off the table.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.18,1:24:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So he says, ho, ho, ho, bad ulcer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.18,1:24:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.89,1:24:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ho, ho.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.39,1:24:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ho, ho, bad ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.39,1:24:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.71,1:24:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the third treatment, it was healed.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.71,1:25:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In three treatments, I'd had it for over 25 years, lived on antacids and antispasmodics,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.21,1:25:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,lived on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.21,1:25:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't drink coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.21,1:25:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me, I drink espresso all day around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.21,1:25:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Would have killed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.21,1:25:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And three acupuncture treatments and it was healed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.27,1:25:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And anxiety attacks and depression attacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.27,1:25:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was healed by stopping eating sugar and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.27,1:25:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Functional hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.27,1:25:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You eat sugar, it goes way up, releases insulin, your sugar drops way down.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.27,1:25:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you get the shakes, you get angry, you get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.34,1:25:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Saturday night, I used to always have a double chocolate sundae.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.34,1:25:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Sunday, I would get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.34,1:25:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent at least a year or two before I discovered what it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.34,1:25:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Sunday, depressed, feeling horrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.34,1:25:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the minute I stopped eating that, it was gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.34,1:25:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped eating that double hot-faced chocolate sundaes and the depression disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.34,1:25:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with anxiety attacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.34,1:25:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these are some of the things I'm going to be talking about later in the year because
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.34,1:26:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they're having a meeting here at Restorative Medicine and we're going to recall some of these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.34,1:26:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I really mean to say is I always get a second opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.34,1:26:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all the alternate methods that people have used.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.34,1:26:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They've used the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.34,1:26:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know people in the Course in Miracles that have recovered from just about every disease known to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.34,1:26:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the 12-step formula.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.75,1:26:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the 12-step programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.75,1:26:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Use Stop Eating Sugar and Sweets if you're depressed and anxious.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.75,1:26:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here depressed or anxious at times?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.97,1:26:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you ever try Stop Eating Sugar and Sweets?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.10,1:26:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.10,1:26:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing to try.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.10,1:26:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a second opinion?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.60,1:26:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're talking to a double hot-faced sundae man right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.56,1:26:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm going to do when they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.56,1:26:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, you've only got a couple of days left to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.75,1:27:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring on the double hot-faced chocolate sundae.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.97,1:27:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll leave the world with a happy smile on your face.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.97,1:27:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Full of hot fudge.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.44,1:27:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Functional hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.69,1:27:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to quit because we're going to do a longer question and answer period.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.69,1:27:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had a good friend who weighed 400 pounds and came from a well, a great family.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.09,1:27:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I met him through some exclusive channels.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.09,1:27:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, he had a terrible problem abusing his wife, alcohol and abuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.09,1:27:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I, and he would try AA and he would get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.22,1:27:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So I told him, I said, you've got functional hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.65,1:27:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you stop eating sugar and sweets, you'll be cured.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.65,1:27:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he hated the idea, but he tried it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.92,1:27:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By God, he got sober.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.92,1:27:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He stopped beating up his wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.92,1:27:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He did very fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.92,1:28:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't like being off sugar and sweets because he was a sugar freak, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.05,1:28:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.05,1:28:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I would watch him at a dining room table.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.05,1:28:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The way he would look at the dessert, you just got the energy of it, like rapacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.05,1:28:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, ooh.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.05,1:28:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, he went to see a well-known medical doctor who was, I think at the time, head of the National Alcoholism Association.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.30,1:28:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And she told him, poo-poo, hypoglycemia is not medically proven.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.30,1:28:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he said, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.30,1:28:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Started eating sugar and sweets.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.30,1:28:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon got drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.30,1:28:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon assaulted his wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.30,1:28:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And soon died.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.50,1:28:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.50,1:28:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead, drunk, abusive, and dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.50,1:28:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All from poo-pooing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.50,1:28:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So alternative medicine can be of enormous value.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.50,1:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I had acupuncture for the fractured three vertebrae.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.59,1:28:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had acupuncture for the ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.59,1:28:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It cured both things.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.59,1:28:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't cure everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.59,1:29:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried it for migraine headache, and it didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.59,1:29:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.59,1:29:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But then along, having good karma, I lived in an age where Imitrex got invented.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.59,1:29:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I discovered Imitrex, and that cured the headache.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.59,1:29:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But before that, nothing cured the headache.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.59,1:29:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.59,1:29:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even codeine.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.59,1:29:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.59,1:29:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing cured migraine headaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.59,1:29:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes every day for three months, one time for three months, every single day I had migraine headache.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.59,1:29:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are just the karmic things that we inherit by virtue of being human.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.03,1:29:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus what we've picked up over previous lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.03,1:29:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus whatever voluntary kinds of spiritual work we have offered to do for others and may well have forgotten about.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.03,1:29:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we have our responsibility and our commitment to our group.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.03,1:29:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Often unstated.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.03,1:29:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Often unstated.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.03,1:29:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or else, if stated, you have to sign a vow and sign a paper or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.03,1:29:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But here it's strictly voluntary.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.03,1:30:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We come together because we have an enormously strong bond.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.03,1:30:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have an enormously powerful spiritual energy, as you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.03,1:30:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We are helping lift the consciousness level of America itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.03,1:30:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought we'll take a break and we'll give a little longer to question and answer period.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.03,1:30:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything I haven't covered, I tried to cover some general areas that we have sort of slided over in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.03,1:30:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that we could conclude them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.64,1:30:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.73,1:30:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take a how long break?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.73,1:30:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.73,1:30:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten to fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.81,1:30:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten to fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.81,1:30:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.81,1:30:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.81,1:30:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll do questions and answers and we'll have a little more time for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.32,1:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When we finish all those slides, we have 99 slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.32,1:30:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was number 99, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.32,1:30:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,99.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.32,1:30:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,99.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.53,1:30:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.53,1:30:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The next slide we do will be number 100.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.53,1:31:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Don.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.64,1:31:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.64,1:31:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.64,1:31:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in your coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.64,1:31:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.64,1:31:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to sign it?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.64,1:31:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.97,1:31:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.97,1:31:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to open it though.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.97,1:31:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.93,1:31:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.93,1:31:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.13,1:31:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,December 06.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.13,1:31:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.13,1:31:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been doing this for six years.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.44,1:31:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.44,1:31:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.44,1:31:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Wowzy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.44,1:31:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one was in, I think, early December.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.44,1:31:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in Prescott Valley.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.44,1:31:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.64,1:31:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you had over 500 people show up that got you an idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.64,1:31:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That maybe these things might help people.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.64,1:31:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm really grateful for the six years of being able to come and learn and be in
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.64,1:31:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,your presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.64,1:31:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it's been a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.64,1:31:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.64,1:31:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.93,1:31:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.93,1:31:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.93,1:31:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.60,1:31:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.60,1:31:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.60,1:31:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.60,1:31:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.10,1:31:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.10,1:31:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.10,1:31:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.10,1:31:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.10,1:31:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.23,1:31:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.23,1:31:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.23,1:31:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.23,1:31:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.23,1:31:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.73,1:32:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.38,1:32:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.38,1:32:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I find great about unity church, is the certificates.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.38,1:32:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think at a great level, I think, many also wait and say, ooh, am I not a serious
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.89,1:32:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,man.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.89,1:32:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you're a great man.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.89,1:32:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole crowd took a hush.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.73,1:32:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.81,1:32:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, this is really good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.57,1:32:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was the bad guy of the era, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.92,1:32:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Timothy McVeigh.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.06,1:32:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mad bomber, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.78,1:32:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the mad bomber, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.98,1:32:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.85,1:32:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I missed the October seminar, and that's when my question comes in.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.01,1:33:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to be with some Hopi elders and some Cherokee elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.43,1:33:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Some what?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.81,1:33:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Hopi and Cherokee elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.48,1:33:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.63,1:33:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing some ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.28,1:33:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a miracle I forgot to mention.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.94,1:33:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.21,1:33:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit closer, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.68,1:33:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Hopi had been on the mesas for thousands of years doing ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.18,1:33:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're coming into a time period here in 207 that they say is a very important time.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.02,1:33:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.11,1:33:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate predictions of time periods and things like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.64,1:33:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We may all be saying goodbye here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.19,1:33:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, this is positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.46,1:33:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I was meant by something positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.52,1:34:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So my gift to you today is some medicine from that gathering.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.02,1:34:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were talking about how the Karmapa will be coming in 207 to coming to Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.97,1:34:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know you had spent some time studying with the Karmapa, I think, when he came through Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.27,1:34:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.00,1:34:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.38,1:34:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is, it seems like you were talking today about the synergies and the blocks that we need to all work on in letting go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.50,1:34:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this preparation, I think everyone right now seems to be, we're going through a time period that's calling for us all to what we call an AA,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.94,1:34:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.22,1:34:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.28,1:34:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.35,1:34:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.40,1:34:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.43,1:34:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.44,1:34:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.47,1:34:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.48,1:34:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.89,1:34:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On a deeper level of step four, surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.06,1:34:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And the surrender I'm going through right now is maybe moving up to a small mountain town up near Strawberry.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.97,1:35:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you have any advice?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.39,1:35:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.78,1:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.52,1:35:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's far away from a major metropolitan area.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.94,1:35:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's also smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.48,1:35:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But it reminded me of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.81,1:35:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And miracles, I forgot to mention one today.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.64,1:35:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.64,1:35:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.06,1:35:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.11,1:35:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention one today.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.27,1:35:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention one today.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.31,1:35:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention one today.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.43,1:35:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.56,1:35:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It rained snake-eyed snow.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.63,1:35:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was the last one that I think they allowed white men, because white men were drunk and disorderly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.98,1:35:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, when we went, it was up in Old O'Reilly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.43,1:35:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute till I finish.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.35,1:35:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was up in Old O'Reilly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.34,1:35:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't rained in, I forget, four months, six months or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.00,1:35:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Old O'Reilly is up on the top, and then there's a cliff that drops off, and the crops grow down below.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.97,1:35:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had some corn that I was given by a white bear,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.21,1:35:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I planted it Hopi style, you know, six inches down.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.57,1:36:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so anyway, I went up for the snake dance,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.27,1:36:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and they said there were hardly any white men there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.00,1:36:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody was sitting on the top of these hogans.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.26,1:36:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And as they assembled, the, what do you call it, dancers started.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.10,1:36:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ones, the...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.72,1:36:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopi dancers?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.68,1:36:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kachinas?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.44,1:36:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.05,1:36:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The kachina dancers?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.14,1:36:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, the antelope dancers, antelope dancers came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.88,1:36:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the old, the best seats there, it was crowded.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.10,1:36:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The best seats were saved for the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.11,1:36:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the antelope dancers began to dance,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.80,1:36:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders came out with umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.97,1:36:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't rained in four to six months.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.67,1:36:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Hopi, the elders came out
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.14,1:36:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.28,1:36:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, umbrellas?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.10,1:36:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't rained in six months.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.18,1:37:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the antelope dancers danced, the clouds began to collect.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.46,1:37:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the time the snake dancers came out, it was raining.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.22,1:37:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Raining just on Old Aravi.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.84,1:37:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,From the cliff, the town is here,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.88,1:37:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the cliff, and then the crops are way down low.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.00,1:37:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So help me God, the rain was raining on the crops.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.35,1:37:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And not on the town of Old Aravi.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.35,1:37:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.61,1:37:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.46,1:37:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So they know how to somehow work the synergy of nature
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.77,1:37:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifest that by collective intention in the faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.00,1:37:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The old ones coming out with the umbrellas,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.27,1:37:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it hadn't rained in six months,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.60,1:37:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it looked ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.18,1:37:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the rain began to fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.56,1:37:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I witnessed it and experienced it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.56,1:37:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And they let go of the snake.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.98,1:37:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the snake ran.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.93,1:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It ran over to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.05,1:37:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then went right by.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.18,1:38:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody was afraid of the snakes at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.81,1:38:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.27,1:38:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've learned from the Native Americans, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.81,1:38:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.15,1:38:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.13,1:38:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.07,1:38:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, I would like to thank you and Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.26,1:38:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for being my teachers for the last three years.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.43,1:38:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.47,1:38:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the question I have is,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.75,1:38:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.64,1:38:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.81,1:38:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I started a serious AA 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.52,1:38:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've worked real hard on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.85,1:38:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.65,1:39:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,do I move forward into A Course in Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.60,1:39:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this something that would enhance my...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.96,1:39:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a 12-step program now?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.84,1:39:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.19,1:39:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.10,1:39:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to follow it up with A Course in Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.72,1:39:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.18,1:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if this is...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.88,1:39:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very often done.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.03,1:39:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people in either group
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.89,1:39:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to co-mingle with those in the other group.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.46,1:39:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't mess up my AA program to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.77,1:39:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.38,1:39:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't mess up your AA.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.23,1:39:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.35,1:39:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.84,1:39:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,AA calibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.46,1:39:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook of A Course in Miracles calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.02,1:39:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that big a jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.93,1:39:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.43,1:39:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty easy to take the third step
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.53,1:39:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on everything as it occurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.22,1:39:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.84,1:39:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything as it occurs,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.96,1:39:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.18,1:39:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You take the third step on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.55,1:39:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So a follow-up in this is something that...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.01,1:39:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It would just enhance...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.97,1:39:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.89,1:39:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you do the third and the 11th step,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.48,1:40:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't really need anything beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.77,1:40:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.86,1:40:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe as a consequence of doing the third and the 11th,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.05,1:40:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you're led to do the A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.36,1:40:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.14,1:40:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.78,1:40:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.14,1:40:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.97,1:40:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have one little small other question.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.31,1:40:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In one of the previous lectures,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.14,1:40:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you had mentioned that the number of...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.85,1:40:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes that people have reincarnated is around six.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.76,1:40:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I misunderstand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.46,1:40:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we were asking the average.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.23,1:40:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask the average.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.81,1:40:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.13,1:40:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is an exceptional group.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.75,1:40:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say the average human
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.21,1:40:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,has already had about six lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.52,1:40:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it says.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.64,1:40:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this group?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.13,1:40:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you have an average?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.35,1:40:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This group, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.14,1:40:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.35,1:40:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.09,1:40:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This group may have had...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.10,1:40:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had many more.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.78,1:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.18,1:40:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This group...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.94,1:40:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.53,1:40:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.93,1:40:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.98,1:41:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've been hanging around a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.52,1:41:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.51,1:41:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.81,1:41:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to ask you for your blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.28,1:41:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.68,1:41:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored by your presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.89,1:41:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.17,1:41:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibration of your life when you're born
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.06,1:41:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is set at birth?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.22,1:41:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.59,1:41:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the time of your death is set?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.56,1:41:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's what we get.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.17,1:41:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.64,1:41:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.71,1:41:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that time as in relative to time itself
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.60,1:41:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it relative to karmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.31,1:42:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have done in that lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.19,1:42:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.64,1:42:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.10,1:42:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You already have a level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.89,1:42:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of birth through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.19,1:42:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So without previous lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.64,1:42:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how would you...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.11,1:42:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you have acquired it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.30,1:42:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.13,1:42:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the time...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.98,1:42:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it wouldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.77,1:42:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The time of your leaving
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.40,1:42:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is sequential time,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.22,1:42:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,not clock time or just...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.21,1:42:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would be like after having fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.28,1:42:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this and that and the other thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.90,1:42:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,now you can leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.52,1:42:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.90,1:42:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.14,1:42:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.64,1:42:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get busy suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.09,1:42:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.31,1:42:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.18,1:42:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, he's still signing.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.40,1:42:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.27,1:42:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you fulfill...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.40,1:42:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so when you have fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.82,1:42:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,certain karmic tasks or obligations,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.59,1:42:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're free to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.47,1:42:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.23,1:42:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.14,1:42:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.00,1:43:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you struggle and resist,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.64,1:43:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to stay longer, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.00,1:43:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.88,1:43:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I ain't forgiving that guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.72,1:43:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.15,1:43:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.68,1:43:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.68,1:43:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.85,1:43:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you keep getting all these books?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.38,1:43:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Gabe keeps giving them to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.96,1:43:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he graces me a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.13,1:43:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, you bet.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.43,1:43:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.90,1:43:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.64,1:43:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,About 15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.32,1:43:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the summer of 1991,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.18,1:43:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,my wife and I went to Charts in France.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.18,1:43:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Charts Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.77,1:43:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Charts Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.19,1:43:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.68,1:43:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We had the great opportunity to walk the circle.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.42,1:43:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.11,1:43:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.85,1:43:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.19,1:43:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, the chairs were pulled up when you were there.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.73,1:43:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They were bowed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.52,1:43:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They put the chairs there
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.72,1:43:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,every time we've been there,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.73,1:43:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can't walk it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.00,1:43:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit different now,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.27,1:44:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had picked up a poster
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.73,1:44:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wanted to present to you and Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.38,1:44:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for Christmas back then.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.64,1:44:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.02,1:44:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.76,1:44:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that gorgeous?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.96,1:44:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.10,1:44:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.22,1:44:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.23,1:44:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.69,1:44:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one of the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.26,1:44:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.02,1:44:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The windows inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.84,1:44:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.27,1:44:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.85,1:44:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, it is my favorite cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.61,1:44:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought maybe if you would put it inside your home somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.07,1:44:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be great,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.60,1:44:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and if not,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.64,1:44:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in your pickup truck where your shotgun goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.97,1:44:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you could hang it on that rack there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.60,1:44:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did have a question for you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.65,1:44:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.39,1:44:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Relating to the Course of Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.43,1:44:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when you took the Course of Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.35,1:44:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what was the biggest blockage that you had
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.47,1:44:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in absorbing the information at the time?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.86,1:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.02,1:44:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.22,1:45:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just enthused about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.38,1:45:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes the phraseology,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.96,1:45:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have to think out the phraseology,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.64,1:45:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but the basic concept was already experiential, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.35,1:45:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see things differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.31,1:45:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see people as innocent,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.94,1:45:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then you don't have to worry about hating them
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.85,1:45:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or being angry or revenge,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.43,1:45:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see they can't help being anything
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.88,1:45:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,other than what they are at this point in their evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.50,1:45:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.31,1:45:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.19,1:45:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.26,1:45:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.27,1:45:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.34,1:45:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.35,1:45:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.38,1:45:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.39,1:45:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.42,1:45:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.43,1:45:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.46,1:45:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.47,1:45:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.50,1:45:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.52,1:45:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.57,1:45:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.18,1:45:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any resistance to anything in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.11,1:45:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanted to thank you for everything you've done
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.02,1:45:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for the last four years for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.50,1:45:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.43,1:45:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.30,1:45:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.81,1:45:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take a picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.09,1:45:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.40,1:45:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.05,1:45:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no dollar, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.89,1:45:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't say that as a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.22,1:46:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's five.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.39,1:46:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.85,1:46:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.42,1:46:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.31,1:46:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.35,1:46:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.44,1:46:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.48,1:46:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.55,1:46:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Najas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.56,1:46:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Following you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.72,1:46:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.75,1:46:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.77,1:46:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.81,1:46:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.93,1:46:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was similar going here.
